This paper deals with the characterization of degrees of freedom (DoF) in a multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) communication system, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the use of full-duplex MIMO transceivers and the consideration of different message configurations suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The optimization of antenna configurations and the use of beamforming techniques further suggest that the paper may be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of MIMO technology and the consideration of different message types also suggest that the paper may be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the construction of achievable schemes for the different message configurations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the computer communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
